  "text": "the eigenvalues of A = B \u03b2 B T \u03b2 are distributed according to (1) (see [CITATION_1] ). We are interested in the behavior of X f,A as n \u2192 \u221e with (n 1 + n 2 \u2212 2n) growing linearly in n and with \u03b2 fixed. This is the only scaling regime in which the limiting spectral distribution is truly Jacobi.",
